{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Transparency and member resources · OIATC{% endblock %}
{% block description %}Members have the right to see how their governments and systems work. OIATC's transparency program helps them use it: organization explainers, records requests, and responsible disclosure, done with documentation discipline.{% endblock %}
{% block og_title %}Transparency and member resources{% endblock %}
{% block og_description %}Members have the right to see how their governments and systems work. OIATC helps them use it: org explainers, records requests, responsible disclosure.{% endblock %}
{% block body_class %}route-program-member-resources{% endblock %}

{% block head_styles %}{% include 'partials/funder-styles.html.twig' %}{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<article class="fund-wrap fund-wrap--narrow">

  <p class="fund-eyebrow">OIATC program</p>
  <h1>Transparency and member resources</h1>
  <p class="fund-lede">Members have the right to see how their governments and systems work. This program helps them use it. We turn public records into resources a member can read, and we show what each one lets you ask for and how.</p>

  <div class="fund-body">
    <p>The work is documentation, not grievance. Financial transparency filings, organization charts, records requests, and responsible disclosure are ordinary instruments of accountable government. We assemble them carefully, source every fact, and present them with the discipline a member or an official can rely on.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>The work, by stage</h2>
    <ul class="fund-links">
      <li><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--live">Live</span> <a href="/explainers/how-sagamok-is-organized">How Sagamok is organized</a> <span>· a member's map of governance, administration, and the band-owned companies, from public records</span></li>
      <li><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--live">Live</span> <a href="/support/records-request">The records request</a> <span>· a member records request and how to add your voice</span></li>
      <li><span class="fund-stage fund-stage--live">Live</span> <a href="/disclosure/sagamok-portal">Responsible disclosure</a> <span>· a member-portal exposure, disclosed responsibly</span></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <h2>The fundable next step</h2>
    <div class="fund-body">
      <p>Funding extends this documentation discipline to more Nations that ask for it: more public records turned into resources members can use, every fact sourced. The work is built to be repeatable, not one-off. The organization explainer already lays out what a member can ask for, from the current organization chart to the published remuneration and audited statements.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="fund-more">
    <p class="fund-more__k">More from this program</p>
    <div class="fund-more__links">
      <a href="/explainers/how-sagamok-is-organized">How Sagamok is organized</a>
      <a href="/support/records-request">Records request</a>
      <a href="/disclosure/sagamok-portal">Responsible disclosure</a>
      <a href="/support">Support this program</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</article>
{% endblock %}
